  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2011-02-08",
    "date": "2011-03-03T18:57:20Z",
    "text": "Consumer Protection Act of 2011 - Invalidates as a defense to a tort claim in any court in the United States that a manufacturer of a product has fulfilled that manufacturer's duty of care when providing all of the necessary information to a learned intermediary, who then interacts with the consumer of the product.\n\nDefines a \"learned intermediary\" as a person licensed under applicable state or federal law to advise a consumer whether or not to use the product in question."
  },
